# Agency engine — Ollama Cloud credentials.
# Copy to `.agency.env` and fill in real values. `.agency.env` is gitignored.
#
# WHY THIS IS A SEPARATE FILE (not .env), for LOCAL dev:
# config.py uses pydantic-settings 2.14 with extra="forbid". That forbids
# extra KEYS IN THE .env FILE — so putting AGENCY_OLLAMA_* in .env crashes the
# app on boot (and the pydantic ValidationError trace echoes the API key value
# into the log). Keeping them here means config.py never parses them.
# agency_engine._cfg() reads this file directly via a hand-rolled parser (NOT
# os.environ, NOT python-dotenv) — the key stays out of the process environment
# entirely on your local machine.
#
# FOR PAAS DEPLOY (Render / Railway / Fly):
# Do NOT use a file. Set these three as environment variables in the host's env
# UI. This is SAFE there — pydantic-settings only applies extra="forbid" to keys
# in the .env file, NOT to process env vars, so unknown env vars set in the host
# UI are ignored by config.Settings and read by agency_engine._cfg() via
# os.getenv. No config.py change is required. Verified 2026-07-13: config.Settings
# boots OK with AGENCY_OLLAMA_* in process env.

AGENCY_OLLAMA_URL=https://ollama.com
AGENCY_OLLAMA_API_KEY=replace-with-your-ollama-cloud-key
AGENCY_OLLAMA_MODEL=glm-5.2
# Optional: per-call timeout in seconds (default 120)
# AGENCY_OLLAMA_TIMEOUT=120